uman resources  and student systems  IT provides the VMI Faculty and Staff with Help Desk support  hardware and software recommendations as well as installations  troubleshooting  and training classes  IT is responsible for the VMI Local Area Network  and can provide access upon request  VMI furnishes a significant number of computers for cadet use in academic buildings and laboratories and provides personally owned computer support for cadet owned laptops  Further information may be obtained by contacting the IT Help Desk at 540 464 7643 or by email at help vmi edu  Access to computer systems and networks owned or operated by the Virginia Military Institute impose responsibilities and obligations upon users  For more information regarding user responsibilities review the Appropriate Use Policy  Post View Self Service Portal Cadet Alumni Email Faculty Staff Email Change Network Password Password Requirements Security Awareness Training Appropriate Use Policy Friendly URLs The mission of the Department of Information Technology  IT  is to help plan  implement  serve  secure and support the technology needs of the Institute and facilitate creativity in teaching  learning  and communication for cadets  faculty  administration  and staff  The goal and intent of the VMI information systems is to enhance educational and research work and to facilitate administrative processes in a secure manner to protect the information of a sensitive nature  such as  social security numbers  bank account and credit card numbers  and intellectual property like cutting edge research  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of respon